Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance covering a possible damage caused by the driver includes a high cost, which in turn depends on different factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driving licence, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
To own a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we're dealing with here.
Auto insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the insured premium agreed and is obliged, in return for damages, to present the amount of the compensation in question.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which consists of several factors, such as age, gender, the time of the creation of the driving licence, family status, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance undertakings set their prices according to the statistics so that higher contributions will also be paid in the event of a higher risk of accident.
For this reason, more than 25-year-olds as well as women need to make fewer contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate due to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and accordingly also according to the company's convictions, they tend to be less accidents than single persons.
The benefits attached to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In establishing the premium, insurance must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver also needs to study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
At this point, we are now listing the most important points that should be considered when choosing insurance in order not only to make a performance-oriented choice but also to make a price-oriented choice.
The 25-year-olds are faced with numerous obstacles in choosing cheap insurance, such as low driving practices and young driving licences.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance policy to take out full insurance, there are nevertheless cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can select a full case with self-share, so that the benefits of full insurance are covered, but at a low price.
This type of contract requires the customer to pay part of the amount resulting from the damage himself.
The amount is determined prior to the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium , which is higher than the amount to be paid , explains Luis Noguera , the main representative of Spain at First Europe , an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is the extended insurance, which assures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused by the own car.
This type of insurance would also cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's a advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is up to you to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to be careful about driving and avoiding accidents.
A credit card is a reduction in the base rate of the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in tariffs said.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on society and its income.
If the company has a successful year behind it, it may allow to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. Reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is most appropriate to opt for full-time insurance with self-share.
Usually young people cannot benefit from their past experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, the Spanish President of the European company explains and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out full insurance; of course only if the financial situation of the individual allows.
Along with the insurers, couples with children are deemed to be customers with the lowest accident rate, and consequently their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, full insurance with self-share (in the case of an amount of EUR 300) would be the best option. In the case of high credit, an extended insurance policy should be used only for the third vehicle year.
They are generally more relaxed and possess a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it offers to take out full insurance with self-share (with an amount of EUR 150) or an extended insurance, which only applies with a sufficiently high credit.
Finally, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough choice that corresponds to our personal situation.
