Now the European "Venus Express" probe has been proven - it detected electromagnetic waves on the edge of the atmosphere: The lightnings on Venus shoot at a height of about 56 kilometers from cloud to cloud, Christopher Russel reports from the University of California in Los Angeles in the science magazine "Nature".
According to the famous "Ursuppen theory", lightning has created life on earth: thunderstorms should have stimulated reactions in the ocean that led to the formation of amino acids, the building blocks of life.
