The second innermost planet of the solar system has almost the same mass as the earth and is almost as large with a diameter of 12,100 kilometers.
The planet, also known as the morning or evening star, crisscross the sun in almost 225 days.
But he turns around much slower: A Venus day takes 243 days on earth.
Although the Venus with surface temperatures of 460 degrees Celsius and a pressure of 92 bar is hardly reminiscent of the Earth, scientists assume that both planets were formed under quite similar conditions.
